<div id="batch-loader-control-panel" class="reports-inner">

<% increment_tab_index(0) %>
<h4>Loading Batch Data into Taxonomy</h4>
Batch data is imported (from parsed Word documents) as <code>loader-name</code> records
<h5>Steps</h5>
<ol>
  <li>Query and view <code>loader-name</code> records to see how well they match with existing <code>name</code> records.
    <ul>
      <li/>You can edit the loader-name <code>simple_name</code> to fine-tune the set of matching <code>names</code> (original value is retained in <code>simple_name_as_loaded</code>)
     <li/>Create <code>name</code> records if no match exists
     <li/>Delete <code>loader-name</code> records if it's not required
     <li/>Exclude a <code>loader-name</code> record from further processing at any time (reversible)
     <li/>Create new raw loader-name records via New &gt; Loader Name to supplement the import
     <li/>Ensure any potential matching <code>Name</code> records have a primary instance
     <li/>View misapplication matches to a <code>name</code> broken down to specific instances - to let you see and choose where the misapplication occurred
   </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Set <b>preferred match(es)</b> for loader-names - locking them to the appropriate <code>name</code> record</li>
    <ul>
     <li/>Edit the match if you need to adjust the relationship instance
    </ul>
  <li>Identify an instance that documents the usage of the loader-name for the taxonomy.</li>
  <li>If no such instance exists, <b>create one</b>.</li>
  <li><b>Add</b> the identified instance to the draft taxonomy.</li>
</ol>

<%= divider %>
<h4>Default Batch Summary Counts</h4>

<% if session[:default_loader_batch_id].blank? %>
  No default batch selected.
<% else %>
  Default batch: <%= session[:default_loader_batch_name] %>
  <br>
  <%= link_to 'Refresh Summary Counts', loader_batch_stats_path(session[:default_loader_batch_id]), {class: 'btn btn-primary', title: 'Stats for the current batch', remote: true} %>
  <div id="batch-stats">
  </div>
<% end %>

</div>
